This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with word embeddings, which are a central component of natural language processing (NLP) and machine translation. Additionally, the paper proposes a new model for neural machine translation (NMT), which is a subfield of NLP. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Furthermore, the paper proposes a method for reducing the number of model parameters, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Finally, the paper involves experiments with language pairs written in different alphabets, which could suggest that it belongs to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as well, since computer vision often involves working with images in different languages and scripts.
